iled. In doing so, these adventurers defy boundaries-between migrant and citizen, center and periphery, neighbor and stranger-that have shaped urban planning and immigration policy. Adventure Capital offers a new understanding of contemporary migration and belonging, capturing the central role that West African migrants play in revitalizing French urban life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aImmigrantszFrancezParis. 0aRacismxEconomic aspectszFrancezParis. 0aWest AfricanszFrancezParis. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aconfront police harassment.  acontemporary migration and belonging.  acreate economic opportunities.  aforge connections to people.  agare du nord.  ahub for west african migrants.  ainternational transit center.  aracial inequality in parisian public space.  aretool french transit infrastructure.  arevitalizing french urban life.  aself fashioned adventurers.  awest african migrants.  awest africans and gare du nord.  awest africans.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2019z978311066763940uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520973084zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520973084423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520973084.jpg  a978-3-11-066763-9  UC Press eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK 